WEBVTT

00:24.442 --> 00:26.402
Hello again, everybody, I'm Jim Lampley.

00:26.569 --> 00:28.612
Certain athletes are born enemies:

00:28.779 --> 00:31.032
Bird and Magic. Ali and Frazier.

00:31.198 --> 00:32.908
Nancy Kerrigan and Tonya Harding.

00:33.075 --> 00:36.203
But the fiercest rivalry
was between two fighters from Pittsburgh...

00:36.370 --> 00:38.539
...with the names Razor and Kid.

00:38.706 --> 00:41.250
ANNOUNCER:
The fight of the year! Both men exhausted.

00:41.417 --> 00:43.127
<i>LAMPLEY:
1982, Pittsburgh.</i>

00:43.294 --> 00:46.464
<i>Razor and Kid,
both undefeated top-ranked contenders...</i>

00:46.630 --> 00:48.883
<i>...divide the city in a spectacular war.</i>

00:49.800 --> 00:52.970
ANNOUNCER:
Now Kid's smelling blood, punishing Razor...

00:53.137 --> 00:54.430
...with a relentless fury.

00:55.347 --> 00:58.893
And down goes Razor.
Down goes Razor.

00:59.060 --> 01:00.227
Down goes Razor.

01:00.394 --> 01:01.896
<i>LAMPLEY".
The brutal 15-round bout...</i>

01:02.063 --> 01:05.316
...is <i>still considered one of
the greatest fights of the '80s.</i>

01:05.691 --> 01:07.735
<i>Kid and Razor quickly rose
to superstardom.</i>

01:07.902 --> 01:12.656
<i>And the man behind their meteoric ascent
was the late fight impresario, Dante Slate.</i>

01:12.823 --> 01:15.659
My dad was king of the ring
and bringer of the bling.

01:16.160 --> 01:18.496
And that makes me royalty,
blessed with all his powers.

01:18.662 --> 01:21.957
MAN: Really good, Dante,
but don't look into the camera. Just look at me.

01:22.124 --> 01:24.794
I don't know.
It's better when I'm connecting with people.

01:24.960 --> 01:27.171
MAN: Yeah, I don't think--
- What's up, people?

01:27.338 --> 01:29.173
<i>LAMPLEY".
As the world clamored for a rematch...</i>

01:29.340 --> 01:32.760
<i>...Slate knew that ratings would turn to
dollar signs for both fighters.</i>

01:32.927 --> 01:35.513
ANNOUNCER:
What a turn of events! Unbelievable!

01:35.679 --> 01:37.681
<i>LAMPLEY".
The rematch drew the biggest audience...</i>

01:37.848 --> 01:40.142
<i>...since the Thrilla in Manila
nine years earlier.</i>

01:40.851 --> 01:41.936
ANNOUNCER:
Kid goes down!

01:42.103 --> 01:44.021
<i>LAMPLEY".
But this time, the story was different.</i>

01:44.188 --> 01:48.317
<i>Razor soundly defeated Kid in a lopsided
victory that was over in four rounds.</i>

01:48.484 --> 01:52.363
<i>What lay ahead was the grudge match
that would've brought each fighter millions.</i>

01:52.696 --> 01:55.032
<i>Then came an announcement
that shocked the world.</i>

01:55.199 --> 01:57.868
Today, I'm announcing my
retirement from professional boxing.

01:58.035 --> 01:59.453
[REPORTERS SHOUTING]

01:59.620 --> 02:02.123
The man's a coward.
I'm gonna get my rematch.

02:02.289 --> 02:04.792
You hear me, Razor?
I'm getting my ****ing rematch!

02:04.959 --> 02:08.503
Sharp has declined to comment further
on his decision to this very day.

02:08.670 --> 02:11.257
And sadly, like many
former professional athletes...

02:11.423 --> 02:14.510
...he lost his fortune just years
after his retirement.

02:14.677 --> 02:17.471
<i>Razor went back to Benson
Shipbuilders in</i> 1987...

02:17.638 --> 02:19.640
<i>...where he had worked
before he went pro.</i>

02:19.807 --> 02:25.396
As the spotlight faded, Kid became a pitchman
for everything from Jockey to jock itch.

02:25.563 --> 02:26.564
[ALL CHEER]

02:26.730 --> 02:30.151
<i>Today, he runs a successful car dealership
and a popular restaurant in Pittsburgh.</i>

02:30.317 --> 02:31.360
ALL:
Hey!

02:31.527 --> 02:33.571
<i>LAMPLEY".
Still, one can almost imagine him tonight...</i>

02:33.737 --> 02:35.990
...on <i>the 30th anniversary
of the fight that never</i> was...

02:36.157 --> 02:38.576
<i>...contemplating yet another year
of growing older...</i>

02:38.742 --> 02:41.078
<i>...obsessed with a fight
that never happened...</i>

02:41.245 --> 02:42.663
<i>...and never will.</i>

02:43.205 --> 02:46.584
- And just for the record, I never had jock itch.
WOMAN: Ha, ha.

02:46.750 --> 02:48.085
I'm just a great actor.

02:48.252 --> 02:50.004
[ALL LAUGHING]

03:07.646 --> 03:09.106
Hey, champ. How's it going?

03:09.273 --> 03:11.775
RAZOR: Don't call me "champ."
Come on. I got your "champ."

03:11.942 --> 03:14.612
Ha-ha-ha!
A little early to start drinking.

03:14.778 --> 03:16.197
You still got it!

03:17.489 --> 03:19.241
I got nothing!

03:20.659 --> 03:22.536
[MEN CHEERING AND CLAPPING]

03:22.703 --> 03:25.706
Guys. All right, yeah.

03:25.873 --> 03:27.291
- Walter.
- Hey.

03:27.458 --> 03:30.669
- What the hell is happening?
- You didn't see yourself on TV?

03:30.836 --> 03:33.547
I don't have a TV. Bad for the brain.

03:33.714 --> 03:36.133
There was this thing on
about you and Kid.

03:36.550 --> 03:38.344
Oh, who cares about that?

03:38.510 --> 03:39.887
Man, come on, like...

03:40.054 --> 03:42.056
Why'd you drop out? Seriously.

03:42.223 --> 03:43.557
- You really wanna know?
- Yeah.

03:43.974 --> 03:45.559
Never told anybody this...

03:45.726 --> 03:47.269
...but, deep inside...

03:48.395 --> 03:49.980
...I wanna dance.

03:50.481 --> 03:52.274
- I wanna dance. The Bristol Stomp.
- Ha-ha-ha.

03:52.441 --> 03:55.152
- The Ching-a-Ling. Pony.
- Stop, you really need to get a TV.

03:55.569 --> 03:57.446
You don't know a good thing
when you see it.

03:57.613 --> 03:59.114
[WALTER LAUGHING]

04:09.416 --> 04:12.336
MAN: <i>What's it like?
KID: It's strong, but it goes down easy.</i>

04:12.503 --> 04:14.838
[RIM SHOT ON DRUMS
THEN AUDIENCE LAUGHS]

04:15.005 --> 04:18.175
No, but seriously. Did you know that
Razor Sharp was ambidextrous?

04:18.341 --> 04:19.635
No, I hadn't heard that.

04:19.802 --> 04:23.013
Yeah, you can knock him out
with either hand.

04:23.180 --> 04:26.308
Kind of like how you went down
over and over in that last fight.

04:26.475 --> 04:28.310
AUDIENCE: Ooh.
KID: Got a comedian in the house.

04:28.477 --> 04:31.105
Sir, why do you have to be so rude
to me in my own place?

04:31.272 --> 04:33.274
Easy, Kid, that's a lady you're talking to.

04:34.441 --> 04:37.194
Are you sure, Joey, because this guy's
got a real set of balls on him.

04:37.361 --> 04:38.862
[ALL LAUGH]

04:39.029 --> 04:43.367
Hey, asshole. It's been 30 years
since those fights. Your shit's getting boring.

04:43.534 --> 04:47.037
Look, I wasn't prepared for that fight.
I was arrogant. I was overconfident.

04:47.204 --> 04:48.580
I just didn't train enough.

04:48.747 --> 04:52.376
Unless you call having sexual intercourse
16 times a week adequate training.

04:52.543 --> 04:54.545
But don't worry, honey,
you would've been safe.

04:54.712 --> 04:56.255
AUDIENCE:
Ooh!

04:56.422 --> 04:59.133
Aha! We got a good audience tonight.

04:59.300 --> 05:02.094
- Mr. Conlon, come on. Let me in, man.
LIGHTNING: No, go away!

05:03.554 --> 05:05.639
Hey, what's going on?
What's the problem?

05:05.806 --> 05:08.892
