Second time this week.

05:09.059 --> 05:11.228
Second time? Sorry, Nora.

05:11.395 --> 05:13.939
Lightning, it's me. What's the problem?

05:14.106 --> 05:16.984
LIGHTNING: That degenerate out there!
He replaced my girl, Maria!

05:17.151 --> 05:20.654
Hey, don't say that. You don't even know
the guy. He looks like a nice guy.

05:20.821 --> 05:23.198
LIGHTNING:
No! Maria gives me the sponge bath!

05:23.365 --> 05:26.660
Not this guy.
His hands are like 80 grit sandpaper.

05:26.827 --> 05:29.913
And he's throwing himself into it too much,
if you know what I mean.

05:30.456 --> 05:32.916
Christ, I've never been so clean
in my entire life.

05:33.083 --> 05:34.752
- Hey, I'm just doing my job.
- I know.

05:34.918 --> 05:37.087
LIGHTNING:
Yeah, that's what my scoutmaster said.

05:37.629 --> 05:40.341
Mr. Sharp, we've
had this conversation before.

05:40.507 --> 05:44.094
I appreciate it, but he's just going through
a bad time. He'll get over it.

05:44.261 --> 05:46.430
He's gonna have to start looking
for another facility.

05:46.597 --> 05:48.932
- Okay. No problem.
- Sorry.

05:49.933 --> 05:53.270
LIGHTNING:
Wait, wait, wait. Let me back up. Wait!

05:53.437 --> 05:54.480
[HEARING AID BEEPING]

05:54.646 --> 05:58.942
What kind of man knowingly takes a job
where he's gotta wash another man's balls?

05:59.109 --> 06:01.612
He's a hero as far as I'm concerned, pal. Heh.

06:01.779 --> 06:03.447
You watch that TV show last night?

06:03.614 --> 06:05.032
Yeah, I heard.

06:05.199 --> 06:08.118
- Listen, uh, your thing. Turn it down.
- What?

06:08.285 --> 06:12.331
Oh, the hearing aid.
Goddamn thing drives me crazy.

06:12.498 --> 06:15.667
- Feel like R2-freaking-DZ.
-Heh.

06:15.834 --> 06:18.879
Well, I'm still steamed up
over that show last night.

06:19.046 --> 06:21.298
- You could've beaten that punk.
- Save your breath.

06:21.465 --> 06:23.884
That book is closed.
Why does everybody wanna open that book?

06:24.051 --> 06:27.388
Just forget about it. Let it go.
Sleeping dogs and all that.

06:27.554 --> 06:29.556
They told me about the new meds.
You try them?

06:29.723 --> 06:33.977
They say they'll add a couple of years
to your life. Maybe you'll reach, heh, 1000?

06:34.144 --> 06:37.147
What difference does it make?
I can't afford them and you're not paying.

06:37.314 --> 06:38.732
You done enough already.

06:38.899 --> 06:41.985
Hey. No, no. It's all right. I'll take care of it.
Don't worry.

06:42.152 --> 06:44.196
You're the only one
that's never screwed me over.

06:44.363 --> 06:46.323
That's gotta count for something.

06:46.490 --> 06:49.660
Don't change the subject.
I'm still very, very pissed off at you.

06:50.411 --> 06:54.832
