17:55.658 --> 17:58.411
Hey, Razor, boss needs to see you.

17:59.662 --> 18:01.706
Least you don't have a family, man.

18:04.918 --> 18:06.961
[HIP-HOP MUSIC PLAYING
INDISTINCTLY ON RADIO]

18:08.004 --> 18:09.172
Okay, Razor.

18:09.339 --> 18:11.007
No, done and done.

18:11.174 --> 18:14.052
Hey, hey, look, get off my phone
before you change your mind.

18:14.219 --> 18:16.012
Okay, man. Bye.

18:17.597 --> 18:21.851
I am done with you! That's right.
It is over, you piece of shit.

18:23.394 --> 18:24.854
Hell, yeah!

18:25.188 --> 18:26.523
Yo! Get back in your car!

18:26.689 --> 18:28.942
Ain't my car no more, bitch! Okay?
I'm getting a new one!

18:29.109 --> 18:30.276
[HORN HONKS]

18:30.443 --> 18:32.362
Sorry! I just won a cracker lottery!

18:32.529 --> 18:33.863
Thank you, Jesus!

18:34.531 --> 18:38.576
Thirty years! Thirty goddamn years!

18:38.743 --> 18:42.372
Yes! Yes! Yes!

18:42.539 --> 18:43.540
Yes, yes, yes!

18:43.706 --> 18:45.333
Yes, yes, yes, yes, yes!

18:45.500 --> 18:48.128
Yes! Yes!

18:50.213 --> 18:51.673
Phew.

18:52.048 --> 18:53.758
[PANTING]

18:55.176 --> 18:56.803
I gotta get in shape.

19:22.245 --> 19:25.748
All right, Pittsburgh.
Who's ready to make history, huh?

19:25.915 --> 19:26.916
I love it.

19:27.083 --> 19:30.044
Okay, without further ado,
I'd like to reintroduce to the world...

19:30.211 --> 19:33.339
...Billy "The Kid" McDonnen
and Henry "Razor" Sharp!

19:33.506 --> 19:34.591
Come on, now!

19:34.757 --> 19:36.342
[MILD APPLAUSE]

19:36.509 --> 19:39.012
- Thought you said there'd be a crowd.
- Trust me. Sit.

19:39.179 --> 19:41.181
I want you all to forget two things:

19:41.347 --> 19:44.100
The Rumble in the Jungle,
the Thrilla in Manila.

19:44.267 --> 19:46.102
But what you will never forget...

19:49.272 --> 19:51.149
Grudgement Day! Questions.

19:51.316 --> 19:54.235
MAN 1: Uh, is this fight some kind of joke?
- No, it's not. Next question.

19:54.402 --> 19:57.989
If one of you gets knocked down, is it safe
to say that you've fallen and you can't get up?

19:58.156 --> 19:59.282
[AUDIENCE CHUCKLES]

19:59.449 --> 20:01.910
Okay. Does anybody have a real question?

20:02.076 --> 20:04.871
Razor, who do you think is in better shape?
You or the Kid?

20:05.038 --> 20:06.956
Depends what kind of shape
you're talking about.

20:07.123 --> 20:09.584
- If it's round, he is.
- Ha, ha.

20:09.751 --> 20:13.129
- So who's gonna train you?
- Who's gonna train me? Frankie Brite.

20:13.296 --> 20:14.339
MAN 2: Really?
- Mm-hm.

20:14.505 --> 20:17.967
MAN 2: Isn't he training Geronimo Padilla?
KID: He is, but he's gonna train me too.

20:18.134 --> 20:23.306
What precautions are you taking? At your age,
this really does seem dangerous, even deadly.

20:23.473 --> 20:27.435
Understand something. This fight will be
cleared as if it was any other bout, okay?

20:27.602 --> 20:31.773
- Are either of you worried that you won't pass?
- No, I'm not worried. I had all my shots.

20:31.940 --> 20:33.483
Johnny Walker, Jack Daniel's.

20:33.942 --> 20:35.568
- Jose Cuervo.
- Ha-ha-ha.

20:35.735 --> 20:40.156
Dante, is there any shot this would be
the first fight that features Life Alert necklaces?

20:40.323 --> 20:42.283
[ALL LAUGHING]

20:42.450 --> 20:44.077
You're being very disrespectful.

20:44.244 --> 20:48.164
A man turns 60, all of a sudden he's washed up
and you kick him out of the workplace.

20:48.331 --> 20:52.001
That may have been fine 100 years ago,
when men were dying at the age of 50.

20:52.168 --> 20:55.296
But in this world, it's different.
The elderly are strong.

20:55.672 --> 20:58.174
Their spirit is strong. And they have a voice.

20:58.341 --> 21:01.302
And that voice is in these two men
and they will be heard.

21:01.678 --> 21:03.513
Respect, bitches.

21:03.680 --> 21:04.806
[WHISPERS]
Get up, right now.

21:06.140 --> 21:09.352
- That's the way you sell a fight.
- You bet your old grizzly ass it is.

21:16.025 --> 21:18.069
Hey, Razor.

21:19.320 --> 21:20.989
- Whoa, Sally Rose.
- Hey.

21:21.155 --> 21:23.032
I thought I saw you. I wasn't sure.

21:23.199 --> 21:25.785
- Hey.
- You look good. How you been?

21:25.952 --> 21:26.995
So why you here?

21:27.495 --> 21:29.372
- I came to see you.
- You did?

21:29.872 --> 21:32.000
Why would you want
to do something like that?

21:32.333 --> 21:34.544
To talk you out of this crazy fight.

21:35.378 --> 21:39.132
I know what you mean. It's a little crazy.
You think it's kind of a joke, right?

21:39.507 --> 21:42.468
I just don't want you to get hurt. That's all.

21:48.099 --> 21:49.392
That's good.

21:50.101 --> 21:51.561
Nice seeing you.

21:54.439 --> 21:56.816
How many alcoholic beverages
do you consume?

21:56.983 --> 21:58.901
Normal. Five, maybe six.

21:59.402 --> 22:02.238
- A week?
- Well, maybe a little more than normal.

22:07.660 --> 22:09.746
Ah! Oh, baby Jesus.

22:09.912 --> 22:11.456
It feels normal.

22:11.956 --> 22:13.583
To you, maybe.

22:14.250 --> 22:17.503
Ma-ma-ma-ma-ma-ma.

22:19.047 --> 22:20.923
MAN: There they are.
DANTE: Hey! Ha, ha.

22:21.257 --> 22:23.259
Just like I said. Paragons of health, huh?

22:23.426 --> 22:25.053
KID:
Passed with flying colors.

22:25.928 --> 22:27.430
Clean bill of health.

22:27.597 --> 22:29.057
DANTE:
Not quite "with flying colors."

22:29.223 --> 22:31.601
But it's our paintbrushes
that we painting with.

22:31.768 --> 22:34.937
So look, I'm gonna introduce you
to a guy that's making this happen.

22:35.104 --> 22:38.566
- Lou Camare, our promoter.
- I would've met you at the press conference...

22:38.733 --> 22:42.278
...but Junior begged me to let him
go in front of the cameras by himself.

22:42.445 --> 22:44.572
This face needs solo exposure.
You know that.

22:44.739 --> 22:46.949
You know, my brother's
the doctor who saw you.

22:47.116 --> 22:48.951
And my other brother,
he's the commissioner.

22:49.118 --> 22:52.288
I can get a dogfight sanctioned if I needed to.
This one was tricky.

22:52.455 --> 22:54.665
Are you saying that I can bring
my dog here too?

22:54.832 --> 22:58.086
That's not what he said.
Why do I feel like there's something coming?

22:58.252 --> 23:00.713
DANTE: Here's the thing.
The conference didn't go as planned.

23:00.880 --> 23:03.091
We gotta sell 5000 tickets, baby.
Five thousand.

23:03.257 --> 23:04.926
So I'm gonna need help promoting it.

23:05.093 --> 23:08.096
Not individuals, both of you.
Together. As a group, okay?

23:08.262 --> 23:11.015
I could never spend
more than three minutes with this burn...

23:11.182 --> 23:14.602
...unless I was beating the brains out of him.
KID: He's got it backwards.

23:14.769 --> 23:16.646
He's punch-drunk.
I was smacking him around.

23:16.813 --> 23:18.898
I smacked him from ring post to ring post.

23:19.065 --> 23:22.485
A little too much of this in the head.
Little too much.

23:22.652 --> 23:24.654
- When's the fight?
- Boom.

23:24.821 --> 23:28.658
Hey, listen. Bottom line is this:
If we don't sell tickets, we don't make money.

23:28.825 --> 23:31.119
- No tickets, no money.
-"No tickets, no money." I'm in.

23:31.285 --> 23:35.498
- That's my guy. No ticket, no money.
- No tickets, no money. No money, no fight.

23:35.665 --> 23:37.333
No ticket, no money.

23:37.500 --> 23:40.837
No fight, no money, no tickets.
Either way you put it, all three ways:

23:41.003 --> 23:43.756
No tickets, no fight, no money.
No money, no fight, no tickets.

23:43.923 --> 23:46.008
No fight, no money, no tickets.
What's the third one?

23:46.175 --> 23:47.844
- All three ways.
RAZOR: You got it covered.

23:48.010 --> 23:49.053
What's your problem?

23:49.220 --> 23:52.181
You gonna fight, fight.
You're not gonna fight, don't fight.

23:52.348 --> 23:54.142
You fight,
you have to do these things.

23:54.308 --> 23:57.687
DANTE: The point that I'm making,
in order to do it, we gotta do it together.

23:57.854 --> 23:59.856
Yeah, together. Okay.

24:00.731 --> 24:03.651
<i>ANNOUNCER:
It's show time at the Miroquois Casino.</i>

24:03.818 --> 24:07.155
<i>Slots, entertainment and the best buffet
on the Monongahela River!</i>

24:07.321 --> 24:08.489
<i>Just ask these two.</i>

24:08.656 --> 24:11.701
Whoa, will you get a load
of that hunk of meat?

24:11.868 --> 24:16.497
Hey, watch your mouth, Billy "The Kid"
McDonnen, onetime Light Heavyweight Champ.

24:16.664 --> 24:19.876
I'm right over here.
Right over by the delicious prime rib.

24:20.209 --> 24:23.880
Sorry, Henry "Razor" Sharp,
onetime Light Heavyweight Champ.

24:24.046 --> 24:28.718
I didn't hear you as I am distracted
by this mouth-watering chicken breast.

24:28.885 --> 24:31.554
If you got a gambling problem,
if you're a degenerate...

24:31.721 --> 24:34.390
...I wouldn't come down here
because gambling is a cancer.

24:34.557 --> 24:37.393
Cut! Please just follow the script, Razor.

24:37.560 --> 24:38.686
It's not that.

24:38.853 --> 24:42.398
The pictures make this look glamorous
but it could be a problem for people...

24:42.565 --> 24:44.358
...and I'm saying it should be known.

24:44.525 --> 24:47.361
What is this, improv night at Chuckles?
Come on, say the words.

24:47.528 --> 24:50.031
Well, maybe I just happened
to hit a sore spot, huh?

24:50.198 --> 24:53.034
Didn't you lose 200 grand betting
the Buffalo Bills?

24:53.201 --> 24:56.537
- Who loses the Super Bowl four times in a row?
- I don't know. You.

24:56.704 --> 24:59.582
- I thought they'd win once.
- Maybe you got a talent for losing.

24:59.749 --> 25:02.251
- I got a talent for busting your--
DANTE: Hey, hey!

25:02.418 --> 25:04.837
KID: You're getting personal.
RAZOR: I'm standing here.

25:05.004 --> 25:06.923
<i>RAZOR:
I'm gonna put that shit right up your ass!</i>

25:07.089 --> 25:09.342
Heh. No such thing as bad publicity.

25:09.509 --> 25:12.178
<i>NEWSMAN [ON TV]: Those two ex-fighters
are making news again...</i>

25:12.345 --> 25:14.597
...and <i>are trending on Twitter.
We'll have that--</i>

25:14.764 --> 25:17.141
- What a lot of crap.
- What's the matter?

25:17.308 --> 25:21.395
You gotta fight in 12 weeks, you're doing
stupid publicity stunts. Who's training you?

25:22.605 --> 25:24.774
Well, here's a hint: Somebody I can trust.

25:24.941 --> 25:27.068
Well, that's easy,
because you don't trust nobody.

25:27.235 --> 25:29.111
- I trust you.
- Ha, ha.

25:29.946 --> 25:31.906
Forget it. I'm a dinosaur.

25:32.406 --> 25:34.992
Come on, we did pretty good
for 13 years together.

25:35.159 --> 25:38.955
In case you haven't noticed, I can hardly
take care of myself. I'm like an infant baby.

25:39.121 --> 25:40.623
Except I got three white pubic hairs.

25:41.123 --> 25:43.125
Heh. You can do this.

25:43.292 --> 25:46.462
I haven't got time.
I gotta find myself a place to stay.

25:46.629 --> 25:48.923
You can stay with me
until I find you a new place.

25:49.090 --> 25:51.884
No. Don't spend any more money on me.
I'm almost done.

25:52.051 --> 25:53.803
It's like polishing a turd.

25:54.804 --> 25:57.306
Do you remember the first time
I came to the gym?

25:57.974 --> 26:00.810
Do you remember what you said to me?
I do.

26:01.644 --> 26:04.647
I said, "it looks like the garbage man
forgot to take out the trash."

26:04.814 --> 26:06.899
Heh. Yeah. Something cheerful like that.

26:07.275 --> 26:08.651
Then you said:

26:08.818 --> 26:11.320
"if I take you on, kid, you're stuck with me."

26:11.487 --> 26:12.822
You said that.

26:12.989 --> 26:15.449
Don't quit on me, Light.
I won't quit on you.

26:17.201 --> 26:18.828
Oh, here we go.

26:18.995 --> 26:20.538
Call it.

26:21.998 --> 26:23.165
It's a quarter.

26:23.332 --> 26:26.252
Come on. Light, I need your help.

26:26.419 --> 26:28.671
It'd be fun. One last time.

26:30.006 --> 26:32.508
You know why I said what I did
about the garbage?

26:32.675 --> 26:33.676
No.

26:35.219 --> 26:39.181
I didn't want your head to get swelled up.
You were so goddamn good.

26:44.228 --> 26:45.605
Thanks,buddy.

26:45.771 --> 26:47.440
- Raze?
- Hmm?

26:47.607 --> 26:49.358
Give me my quarter back.

26:50.359 --> 26:51.694
- Seriously?
- Yeah.

26:53.029 --> 26:54.530
How can you be so cheap?

26:54.697 --> 26:57.158
I haven't got any money.
Give me my damn quarter.

26:57.325 --> 26:58.534
Okay. Fine.

27:17.219 --> 27:18.721
Nice car.

27:26.729 --> 27:31.192
Oh, wow! This is exciting. Look who's here
to meet me. Kid McDonnen.

27:31.359 --> 27:34.028
You know him from the Internet.
"Two old guys fighting."

27:34.195 --> 27:37.740
He used to be Light Heavyweight Champ.
Wow, you put on a couple pounds?

27:37.907 --> 27:39.700
- You're gonna get me in shape.
- Oh, really?

27:39.867 --> 27:40.910
He's gonna get me in shape.

27:41.077 --> 27:43.037
- Give us a couple minutes.
KID: They can come.

27:43.204 --> 27:44.872
Watch a real reality show.

27:45.039 --> 27:47.375
- Watch us negotiate.
- Okay. Okay! Ha, ha.

27:47.541 --> 27:50.002
Hey! Ho-ho! All right.

27:50.294 --> 27:52.797
- Let's get real, Kid.
- Okay, let's get real.

27:52.963 --> 27:54.674
Me training you, it ain't happening.

27:56.759 --> 28:00.721
Well, this might be a problem,
because I already made the announcement.

28:00.888 --> 28:02.932
You, my friend, are embarrassing yourself.

28:03.099 --> 28:05.434
A great performer knows
when it's time to get off the stage.

28:05.601 --> 28:09.689
- What? Foreman fought when he was old.
- He was 15 years younger than you.

28:09.855 --> 28:11.273
Listen, you know what I'm gonna do?

28:11.440 --> 28:14.944
I'll go down there and fight
any one of those fighters, the best one.

28:15.111 --> 28:19.573
And then if you see
that I don't have what you want, I'll walk away.

28:19.949 --> 28:21.242
It's over.

28:21.409 --> 28:22.785
Where's your dignity?

28:22.952 --> 28:26.163
You're in my office, begging me
for a comeback you don't deserve?

28:26.330 --> 28:28.791
- Well, take your best shot now.
- Whoa, Kid.

28:28.958 --> 28:30.251
What are you flexing for?

28:30.418 --> 28:32.628
Don't try it. I'm warning you.
I'll lay you out.

28:32.795 --> 28:34.755
- Don't worry, I won't.
- All right.

28:34.922 --> 28:36.465
Oh. Come on, Kid.

28:36.632 --> 28:39.427
- What?
- I saw your fist clench 10 seconds ago.

28:39.593 --> 28:42.221
